[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering testing dependencies**\n\nI'm thinking about whether we need to use reflection directly. The proxy is from the reflection package, but it's a public API, so maybe that's acceptable. I wonder if it could help avoid using Method.invoke, though it might add complexity to testing. Alternatively, I considered using java.beans.EventHandler, but no. I think it might be better to prototype in a test environment with JUnit and use plain Java with the necessary dependencies in Gradle. I'll need to check which jars are required.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0bf38c1e278fd09f0169f293a0a010819c8fbdfaf8cdf2b63d\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8pO3btvCQmc0yXX_bc3Ky4bbyFNSO3uRdWs8twqp0Zd1uzLU74YkQSjR7VG0Hp934u51ApsrSTjN8K7bw4UgAeTWSuOfIdZcVVl-yiGEIKVJ0j83hETqw_1ZNQu_WGrE34P_wq9GupNb43yRXTeAaKIddJ15M5Ylik3aeBW90eSRlqGGYqJS8SEeXKByydNLb31FtuJJHIoQyfl3-ZhUXvZti3UvG3weoDbbMioRDeNURjTs9x5fhrYx-HsmTdhzo76CREIM-B0Z--PdHa1-241fXp_NynV6NodJ3kpetpT5UBHuI8TBWZDVzM6l8YHCEFycrJT8fJU7afSsIU0Lp_cLJ5QfAcvdW0Yd_SvCAoTU-RzP-3mtllzTA0TMYWUgFVRXdn-o83cv9Xj-d7-4Xgl4eJ3s8XPK8O7bC-WbX1iUeCPO4dcyZIwtRydimNcePimtDswm_Yo242nNci5Xi5z4aGUSw6-jwGt3IlgCVaNdCFY9JWS_Kgptd2O0QlVOIogG3UIL9ONfaaybrv0Q7mm6UHcTxbnycB_2FTzGZEbN6ZdfO8yhxmdSzIlvqS2VlTGnLSQAbuY1USUDnN12YeaRjLSc1jbiigSPixGaXka3zAWVoDZRV0JNrfCYEb2srFPK7PJtr_VB2e2ihCTp_7PH6B_DMv61lmBp6GpnH2X0uLI1aYYw4ZbaVDOAlsrRxDMVmQrlu5ZwECu3N2q9gZMtovl1nJYVBaQUMiTPTjwya7_aEzCFCEf2uI0OBNJEG2OGS12JiTgMQkh6f2t04NXPYPjqk9soXd141ClMgC-Rmtrzbli2j2OWSRZWEGAunwJ-FxNPBj6VQ4WUiYHZSuIho0ltoKiRoPdkU-LhUax76zoPsCkfx37dw7NQyh83XkwPRvZnR5SfsrBP2bZZ4IWeS_ZK6riETe0x_IZeAHQt8lCUppdUPTL8vH5mrZy9Q5ZiyBij0LklOjgiPSjESUHjxk6fBZP9AWiYZgVn86-yNmPT6qFjanSYmaRsA5U51e6eK2g4QUztKiL6P4HxaeomxKJDDRwL6QaIdlDdoAPq74-e1eiWxNkso_IzYlmFYxbcBQAOzBGkHMKleZqxfbfb07KNR69NU-S8gGrFsjLnzuw3zKWox1J85t5S7FKDxwU7jeXwHr9N3zJYEb0EyNTQFvfbcJCiDsZ9IaSgtYHE6UZK4M0MB-7