[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Assessing MethodAccess and Proxies**\n\nI'm confirming whether generated MethodAccess could throw an error and if it shows any issues with access being null. It looks like this succeeded as a fallback. Now, concerning native image viability, I'm considering the limitations of dynamic proxies with custom ClassLoader. Runtime generation seems unsupported, and tests need to execute under the native image, which complicates things. It's essential to remember that custom ClassLoader could block MethodAccess if the proxy class isn't pregenerated. So, it might be best to avoid using a custom ClassLoader if I can.\n\n**Exploring BeanSerializer Options**\n\nI'm considering running BeanSerializer in a native image where MethodAccess.get fails due to no dynamic class definition, but JVM tests might need to skip—though skipping native isn’t an option. A test conditional could help, but that seems tricky. I wonder if BlockingLoader could work with a class generated at build time. Issues arise with custom loaders, especially regarding proxy creation in native images. I might need to use a public test bean but prevent MethodAccess through an invalid method signature to navigate these limitations. It's definitely a complicated scenario to analyze!\n\n**Checking Parameter Limits**\n\nI'm exploring the possibility of using a method with more than 255 parameters in Java since that's the max. I think MethodAccess might generate code using BIPUSH for parameter indices, limited to a maximum of 127. So, if the parameter count exceeds 127, it could throw an IllegalArgumentException when trying to visitIntInsn. To test this, I could create a public method with 128 parameters in a bean—since Java allows up to 255 slots, that could be interesting to see in practice!\n\n**Testing method access**\n\nI’m looking into whether ASM allows a BIPUSH with the value of 128. The BIPUSH byte operand is signed, but I'll need to test if ASM checks this. If MethodAccess.get throws an error, I might end up with a null access. The bean has standard getName and setName methods and is native-compatible without a custom loader. I guess I’m going to define a method with something like 130 String parameters returning void. The Java source is long, but that’s okay. Time to test!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0bf38c1e278fd09f0169f293c6a48c819c802a1a31156b6ce4\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8pPRwkiFW-f2uEXoDBMc-_E65FUEf9zg8JzwElD73jCj9Mg9bP8dUZgya9W43X57Y5JIGrAp8feri8pIVb8UQUg2FzsEI2x-e2rbaPy3MmrHUpUtmBUt2m-Z6Wbs65cFTPhNnQ8KyuCWxerFrkLO6W_maSnjxr8jhW4saS792LJzOCDx7RTn32QoBZ6Pb4fS7g2vT-QYWLvz2rKLsQeGezubhGIuZRYLs3gsJGZWJS4ywTBD8PUZ0y_fcTVcvcd3KmxoX2tjrxgruyW3cf0MlJkVq7bvyb6gxaoMKCy7xjAyIUsG7gDfXbzm2fuMXe0DQyRVxZklpvyEaKgqyLtcpfYitVj6uSjqK6BqUwAG6fNEVSdlOjtROlrsAGa1BWGPHaTAk199CvOJCJ9ecpsnDJ7FlX6J0tCe5ZWcGmJg7P_gfTWpgHAQssy3_bFyxjBVFZLXAfZN873wbcSfW6ByRmfaBrSlwuwRwgvVaGcnY0ttv3dqtqAZVT1Ejl5H0Ff0bv1YHQ_5tvDPUdxjbHF0GJAwnG4U-5H7jO3ClSx3EOj1pVmMnWPttNrvjqMM7zrviA4q4S1IjTnY38AwyF6q55XRCSMIoXBZBlgVn7G8NphId1WvG6xoG3q54iHQG9R0_lELorPxfqtCPL001jsUQ_HgJmI-o_ebz1zYV8dd2uOdPeGnphzB36jUnbKQalSSUJD4SPlSzgcTxUgbD9WoWR1jdyKaBgAogb7R-I1Uk5fRnNvcA8qcK7Nv2e2S3Zs6bc_3xJIywqeb0B3ycy2RmLS6vCx1sLMb_KyPa84QjJx_i3WwbZS3V98n1wxL1VykrgrswIChsVSnrAt3_xvJe-1kN_GtREDzmRyWV8bemg76D0UzySKZ0gKbWIq9eZi1KAE134GKd71DiqxQAfX6G1S-0b8BZp9SXnvPWs7_ato_GJRdokBThHnLrA3VJMCsqNAUmWxWPJl9k6c7sJBscgGX45kTBJGOYJlE8STgj5EAX4hl9irAroVOf29exI-MhnKAmsxx_bJk8DZaRzzoDePQyUEw0iBtzusBOgMkDZaq6nDzzpxleCgHpu5T8su3e5isctiaUfkHUxIc6OKArNeg6EB2u-ferkoIeifvckjxepCbA8IAP9u9knEwLH2GABTr2fo3rosNreE70CffFRgI-2Tremnc7TwMeleQqLQqtWTqdCzDUFM4xHpozvyvJIZLeckfAJ09e8kDSGhuIqr3USbavbZpv5FFNn4kPmcv-1UfbmdcWPOo38tpWerbvYoBb8d-GzCIS7cUIdc50xpDxYJyaEkdgyHG8lmCNhOj1yUhmZtoxdzQckqjZXG4NJyr0dtFFvDhDvcWra7BBGbEDAfh1qqpwqyiiFsD-U15S-iMbqQF-f8oLY2CinMmKdDvi49jSpt92I5KtzpvKw4hu9q65U6SMI7NSR7cuybmuOFBZu9tUvqFPj0IWev0UHRH